splitQData

public static String[] splitQData(String data)
Gets the number of rows or columns and the captions from the data of a question datum. Format of data: 
      3 | caption 1 | caption 2 | caption 3

Captions are optional; number of captions needn't match number of rows/columns.

Parameters:
data - the data of the question datum
Returns:
array where the first member is the number of rows and columns, and the remaining members are the captions

Parameters:
data - the data of the question datum
Returns:
array where the first member is the number of rows and columns, and the second member is the joined captions

responseToXML

public static String responseToXML(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request)
Converts the individual values of textboxes from the front end into a single XML string. Values are subjected to unicodeToCERs() and toValidXML(). We use unicodeToCERs() and not inputToCERs() because the input values have already been converted to Unicode by encodeURIComponent().

Parameters:
request - holds the values of the textboxes
Returns:
table in XML format; non-ASCII characters are converted to CERs, as are <, >, ", ', and & when it is not followed by #\d+.

responseToXML

public static String responseToXML(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                                   boolean urisEncoded)
Converts the individual values of textboxes from the front end into a single XML string. Values are subjected to unicodeToCERs() and toValidXML(). We use unicodeToCERs() and not inputToCERs() because the input values have already been converted to Unicode by encodeURIComponent().

Parameters:
request - holds the values of the textboxes
urisEncoded - true if the text was subjected to encodeURIComponent() before being submitted
Returns:
table in XML format; non-ASCII characters are converted to CERs, as are <, >, ", ', and & when it is not followed by #\d+.
